MOUNT MAUNGANUI, New Zealand (AP) — Bangladesh captain Mominul Haque won the toss and chose to bowl Saturday in the first of two tests against New Zealand.Haque said some early moisture in the pitch at Bay Oval is likely to help the tourists’ seam attack.New Zealand is playing a test at home for the first time since beating India in the final of the World Test Championship in England in June.Bangladesh is without Shakib Al Hasan, who asked to miss the tour, and Tamim Iqbal who has a broken thumb. The retirement from test cricket of Mahmudullah also has stripped the team of some of its experience.New Zealand chose spin bowler Rachin Ravindra as its allrounder to support seamers Trent Boult, Tim Southee, Kyle Jamieson and Neil Wagner.Devon Conway returns to the batting lineup after breaking his hand at the Twenty20 World Cup. Tom Latham will lead the home side in the absence of Kane Williamson who is recovering from a persistent elbow injury.ADVERTISEMENT___New Zealand: Tom Latham (captain), Will Young, Devon Conway, Ross Taylor, Henry Nicholls, Tom Blundell, Rachin Ravindra, Kyle Jamieson, Tim Southee, Neil Wagner, Trent Boult.SportsVikings lose Cousins to COVID list before game vs. PackersCincinnati DB Bryant honors late NBA star with number switchHall of Famer Sam Jones, winner of 10 NBA titles, dies at 88Hartman leads No. 20 Wake Forest to 38-10 romp in Gator BowlBangladesh: Shadman Islam, Mahmudul Hasan Joy, Najmul Hossain Shanto, Mominul Haque (captain), Mushfiqur Rahim, Liton Das, Yasir Ali, Mehidy Hasan Miraz, Taskin Ahmed, Ebadot Hossain, Shoriful Islam.___More AP cricket: https://apnews.com/hub/cricket and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports